    <p>PLAYSCAPES SET THE TONE</p>
    <p>At the Khoo Teck Puat-Na­tional Univer­sity Chil­dren’s Med­i­cal In­sti­tute, the “playscape” de­sign ethos be­gins in the lobby with its cav­ernous 14m-high, nat­u­rally ven­ti­lated atrium.</p>
    <p>Dubbed the “cityscape”, it fea­tures small “houses” for reg­is­tra­tion and pay­ment, triage and phar­macy ser­vices. In­stead of con­ven­tional clin­i­cal seats, it has mod­u­lar benches amid ar­ti­fi­cial turf and plants.</p>
    <p>Swedish fur­ni­ture re­tailer Ikea fur­nished the breast­feed­ing rooms and the re­ha­bil­i­ta­tion cen­tre with cheer­ful fix­tures and toys, giv­ing the rooms its Scan­di­na­vian brand of “hygge” or cosi­ness. Dyson Sin­ga­pore pro­vided hand dry­ers with Hepa fil­ters for the public wash ar­eas.</p>

